Sentencas: The present study reports thermal and electrical properties of Sr1-xYxCoO2.5+delta (x = 0-0.40) as a promising cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Thermal and Electrical Stability of Sr0.9Y0.1CoO2.5+δ as a Promising Cathode for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The results show that x = 0.10 is the best composition possessing a single primitive cubic perovskite structure, stable conductivity and the lowest polarization resistance.
Titulo: Thermal and Electrical Stability of Sr0.9Y0.1CoO2.5+δ as a Promising Cathode for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Thermogravimetric analysis indicates an oxygen intake from RT to similar to 375 degrees C, above which oxygen loss occurs.
Titulo: Thermal and Electrical Stability of Sr0.9Y0.1CoO2.5+δ as a Promising Cathode for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The oxygen gain-loss behavior corresponds well with the conductivity increase-decrease trending, reflecting that oxygen-nonstoichiometry controls the hole-concentration (or oxidation-state of Co-ions).
Titulo: Thermal and Electrical Stability of Sr0.9Y0.1CoO2.5+δ as a Promising Cathode for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy analysis further reveals that the overall ORR polarization consists of a faster charge-transfer and a slower surface oxygen exchange.
Titulo: Thermal and Electrical Stability of Sr0.9Y0.1CoO2.5+δ as a Promising Cathode for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
